Subject: Indian Marriage Invitation From: "GradProSkills" <gradproskills@concordia.ca> Date: 2014/1/6 17:39 To: wkkustc@gmail.com
Dear Pankaj,
We cordially invite you and your family to our daughter Deepali’s wedding with Ashish, son of Mr. L.K. Mohan on May 23rd, 2010. We would highly appreciate your esteem presence on this joyous occasion. As you are a part of our family so your presence are highly commendable 3 or 4 days prior to the wedding day. The venue for the wedding ceremony is Pearl Banquet near Mall Plaza at Dwarka in New Delhi. e
A formal invitation card will be sent to you soon but please accept this letter as a personal invitation from our side.
We are looking for your gracious presence with your blessings for the couple. We request you to confirm your arrival at the earliest.
Thank you,
Sincerely,
Usha & Shrish Purohit
